            <title>[SOLR-16944] /api/node/health should be governed by &quot;health&quot; permission</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16944</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The /solr/admin/info/health v1 API (HealthCheckHandler) is governed by &lt;tt&gt;HEALTH_PERM&lt;/tt&gt;, while the new v2 API &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/main/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/handler/admin/api/NodeHealthAPI.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;/api/node/health&lt;/a&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;CONFIG_READ_PERM&lt;/tt&gt;. The V2 API should also use &lt;tt&gt;HEALTH_PERM&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
